}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== Like other '''[[D-Link]]''' rebranded ICs, the DL-2001 seems to be an '''[[IC+]]''' (or rather, '''Tamarack''' [http://www.icplus.com.tw/profile.htm acq. by '''ICPlus''' in 2002]) chip. It uses [http://etherboot.org/pipermail/gpxe-devel/2010-July/000523.html the '''ip1000''' driver, for the IP1000, in Linux].
